<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aoshen Fault at Dying Moments Costs Their Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Ma Jian's last-minute fumble
dealt a heavy blow to the promoted Beijing Aoshen as they were
overtaken by Liaoning Hunters by a margin of two points in the
seventh round of thre China Basketball League on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Aoshen has led the first two quarters but their lead was
diminished until the third quarter when the deficit was reduced
to 70-71.
</P>
<P>
Ma Jian and Wang Sheng almost secure the win for the Beijing
team with their three-pointers before national guard Li Xiaoyong
pulled Hunters back in the game with a long shot and a
breakthrough attack.
</P>
<P>
In the last four seconds Ma Jian was sent off for his sixth
foul and the away team edged past Aoshen 89-87 with consequent
two field shots.
</P>
<P>
The reigning champions Bayi Rockets maintained their
unstoppable lead in the league with once again an one-sided
victory over Guangdong Tigers, the seventh in as many games while
another team from northeast of China Jinin Northeast Tigers
scored a home victory over Sichuan Pandas 101-92.
</P>
<P>
In the other games of the day, Shanghai Sharks edged Jiangsu
Dragons 100-98, Beijing Ducks thrashed Jinan Army Pegasus 85-63
and Shangdong Flaming Bulls beat Zhejiang Cyclone 100-85.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
