<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Hospitalized With Acute Stomach Ulcer Bleeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
was taken to the Central Clinical Hospital Sunday with an acute
stomach ulcer bleeding, the presidential press service said.
</P>
<P>
He is in stable condition but needs to stay in bed, it added.
"According to doctors, an emergency gastroscopy confirmed the
diagnosis. For the present moment his state is stable, a course
of anti-ulcer therapy was appointed," the Itar-Tass news agency
quoted the presidential press service as saying.
</P>
<P>
This was a second time that Yeltsin was hospitalized since
early last December when he was admitted into the same hospital
for pneumonia, after only three hours in the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday ,the 67-year old president planned his first
return to the Kremlin office after the New Year holiday, but
canceled his arrangements without explanation.
</P>
<P>
His spokesman said then that he was in normal health and "is
fit and active."
</P>
<P>
This time, Yeltsin's doctors have "strictly recommended" that
he stay in bed in the coming days, thus throwing in doubt a
France visit scheduled for January 28, his first overseas trip
since last October, when he had to cut short a visit to Central
Asia because of illness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
