<HEADLINE> Turkey Calls for Prevention of 'Massacres' in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkey Sunday called on the
U.N. Security Council to take necessary measures to prevent the
bloody massacre in Kosovo in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said in a statement that Turkey is
"deeply concerned over the reports on the bloody massacre of
45 innocent Kosovar Albanians."
</P>
<P>
"Turkey denounces all forms of repression and acts of violence
regardless of their sources and purposes," said the statement,
adding that Turkey regarded such acts as crimes against humanity
and strongly condemned them.
</P>
<P>
The statement added that "Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem
has brought the issue to the attention of the Secretaries General
of the United Nations and NATO as well as the Chairman-in-Office
of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe."
</P>
<P>
"Cem also suggested that the issue be discussed urgently and
with priority at the U.N. Security Council," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the statement said that Turkey called on the
international community to attach great importance to the solution
of the Kosovo problem through peaceful means without any delay.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
