<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five European Countries Ambassadors Return to Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Ambassadors from five European
countries to Belarus on Sunday returned here, marking the end of
a 9-month diplomatic dispute.
</P>
<P>
They are from France, Germany, Britain, Greece and
Italy.
</P>
<P>
The dispute began in last April, when ambassadors living in
the Drozdy diplomatic compound on the outskirts of Minsk
were evicted by the government of Belarus for repairing the
compound's plumbing and sewage system.
</P>
<P>
The EU member states, the U.S., Japan and other involved
countries were irritated by the move and recalled their
ambassadors in succession for indefinite consultation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
