<DOCNO> XIE19990118.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Museveni Urges Ugandans to Live Peacefully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has urged all people in the country to live peacefully
and in harmony together as the month of Ramadhan reminds all of
us.
</P>
<P>
He made the call in a message congratulating Ugandan Moslems on
the successful completion of the Holy month of Ramadhan, a press
release from the President's Office said Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
In the message, the president extended his personal good wishes
and those of the government to the entire Moslem community in
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
He commended the community for undertaking fasting and prayers
during the month to re-dedicate themselves to the teachings and
principles of Islam which emphasizes discipline, peace and
brotherhood among all mankind.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has a population of roughly 20 million, with 10 percent
of them being Moslems and the rest Christians.
</P>
<P>
Some Moslems were arrested as bombing suspects by the police
authorities in 1998, setting afloat rumors that the government was
against the minority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
