<DOCNO> XIE19990118.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lesotho's Airline to Stop Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho's national air
service, Air Lesotho, will close down on February 6 owing to heavy
losses, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The board of directors of Air Lesotho decided to terminate the
airline's operations following the receipt of a letter from the
chairman of the company, Eddie Absil.
</P>
<P>
SAPA did not say when the decision was made.
</P>
<P>
Absil reported that Air Lesotho had been making losses
averaging 20,000 Rand (3300 U.S. Dollars) a month since it was
established following the privatization of the national airline,
Lesotho Airways.
</P>
<P>
Absil said the losses amounted to about three million Rand
(500,000 Dollars) over the 15-month period of operations of Air
Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
The Air Lesotho management notified the Lesotho government
that it was unable to bear any more losses as the original
expectations of significant increases in passenger traffic on Air
Lesotho routes had not materialized.
</P>
<P>
It was announced at the weekend that the closure of Air Lesotho
 operations would not affect international air traffic between
Lesotho and Johannesburg as a South African airline would keep on
operating this service.
</P>
<P>
However, Lesotho's domestic air services will be terminated on
January 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
