<HEADLINE> Israeli Opposition Leader Attacked Over Spy Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Israeli opposition Labor
Party leader Ehud Barak was criticized by the government Sunday
for his refusal to sign on a letter calling on Washington to
release an Israeli spy.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after a weekly cabinet meeting, Minister
of Immigration and Absorption Yuli Edelstein said Barak's move
will waste the chance for Jonathan Pollard, an ex-U.S. navy
intelligence analyst sentenced to life imprisonment in the U.S. in
1986 for spying for Israel.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu expressed his "great
disappointment" at the cabinet meeting over Barak's decline to
sign on the letter recently initiated by a ministerial committee,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu said he had hoped that the government's effort to
get Pollard released will gain national support, adding that this
is a national issue instead of a political one.
</P>
<P>
Edelstein, who is a member of the ministerial committee, said
that the idea was that a letter signed by the leaders of the
ruling party and the main opposition party will greatly enhance
the chance for Pollard's release.
</P>
<P>
But Barak's office contended that Barak prefers a
behind-the-door approach to settle the Pollard issue, saying
Netanyahu's strategy of launching a public campaign has proven
futile.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton has repeatedly rejected Israel's
plead for the release of Pollard on humanitarian ground.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu has threatened to boycott a signing ceremony of the
Wye River peace deal with the Palestinians in October last year
unless Clinton promised to release Pollard. Clinton rejected the
ultimatum but promised to review the case.
</P>
<P>
Senior aides to the U.S. president have started to submit their
proposals over the issue. But Edelstein said Israel did not know
that they have suggested because some of the aides strongly
opposed the release of Pollard given the severe damage he caused
to the U.S. intelligence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
