</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Foreign Ministry Sunday attacked the Italian
government for allowing Kurdish rebel leader Abdullah Ocalan to
depart from Rome to Russia.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that accompanied by Italian policemen, Ocalan
left his villa in the town of Infernetto, 30 kilometers south of
Rome, and took a plane from Rome's military airport Ciampino to
Moscow around 13:00 local time (1200 GMT) on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan, who was sought after by Turkey, was arrested in Rome on
November 12 last year under international arrest warrants issued
by Germany and Turkey after he arrived on a flight from Moscow.
(BC-Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
