ANKARA -- Turkey's newly formed pro-secular minority government
won a vote of confidence in the parliament here Sunday, thus
ending the near two-month-old political crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
The government led by the Democratic Left Party (DSP) leader
Bulent Ecevit obtained 306 votes in the 550-seat parliament, which
is regarded a clear victory for the veteran politician.
(BC-Turkey-Government)
</P>
