<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia, Cuba Denounce Neglect of U.N. Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Cuba on Monday
indirectly denounced the United States and Britain for bypassing
the United Nations in dealing with international issues,
according to the Interfax News Agency.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement released after talks in Moscow, Russian
Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov and his Cuban counterpart Roberto
Robaina Gonzalez expressed "deep concern" over attempts to upset
the international relations system established by the U.N..
</P>
<P>
These principles, which took shape after World War II and are
based on the U.N. Charter, should be respected by all members of
the world body, stressed the two ministers, indirectly referring
to the bombing last month of Iraq by the United States and
Britain without the approval of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain launched air strikes because the
Iraqi administration refused the U.N. arms inspection team's
access to some sensitive sites which were suspected of being
factories used to produce weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Moscow strongly opposed using force against Iraq without U.N.
approval, but this was ignored by the U.S. and Britain.
</P>
<P>
They "emphasized that the principle of not using force, the
threat of force or any other measure of coercion or diktat
enshrined in the U.N. Charter is imperative in character, is
binding on all states and places a categorical ban on all
military and coercive measures and all other actions, such as
blockades, embargoes and other such actions, that have not been
sanctioned by the world community," said the statement entitled
"In Support of the United Nations".
</P>
<P>
"The charter itself contains direct and clear provisions for
exceptions to the ban, under which the U.N. Security Council
alone enjoys the authority to sanction coercive measures aimed at
maintaining or restoring international peace and security.
</P>
<P>
"Any attempt to bypass the Security Council may undermine the
existing mechanism of peace maintenance, produce chaos in
international affairs and lead to primacy of force over
international law.
</P>
<P>
"A special place in the process of U.N. reforms belongs to
work to rationalize the operation of the Security Council. The
fact that the U.N. Security Council bears the main responsibility
for the maintenance of international peace and security, as laid
down in the Charter, must not be questioned under any
circumstances," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Any decision to enlarge the Security Council must "strictly
comply with the principle of fair geographic representation and
be widely agreed, ideally being based on the consensus of the
U.N. member countries."
</P>
<P>
The ministers said that the U.N. was the "only universal
international organization that is aimed at accumulating efforts
by the world community to agree on principles for the resolution
of conflict situations and the strengthening of the international
security and stability system based on the U.N. Charter".
</P>
<P>
Robaina, who arrived here Sunday evening on a working visit,
is scheduled to meet Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov and
the speakers of both houses of the Russian parliament on
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
