<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Parliament to Start Winter Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The winter session of
Bangladesh's Jatiya Sangsad, the country's parliament, will start
on January 25, the official BSS news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
President Shahabuddin Ahmed will make an inaugural address
explaining the government politics and programs in fulfilling the
constitutional obligation, on the opening day of the 12th session
of the seventh parliament, which was elected in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The session is expected to see fierce debating on the country's
economic situation following the trimming of the Annual
Development Program due to the over-two-month-long flood last
year. The ruling and opposition parties will also deliberate on
the country's crucial political situation with focus on the city
corporation and municipal elections scheduled for late February.
</P>
<P>
On the legislative aspect, the Civil Procedural (Amendment)
Bill 1998, which was passed by the parliament in its last session
and sent to the president for assent, will be placed before the
parliament again for reconsideration.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time in the country that the president
returned a bill with a note of dissent.
</P>
<P>
One fresh bill seeking provision of legal aid to the poor will
be introduced before the parliament, which is expected to deal
with all the 10 bills sent to different standing committees during
its last session last November.
</P>
<P>
The bills include the Bangladesh Law's Revision and Declaration
(Second Amendment) Bill 1998 and the Transplantation of Limbs and
Organs in Human Body Bill 1998.
</P>
<P>
The parliament secretariat has started working ahead of
schedule, as government offices enjoy a three-day holiday for
Eid-ul-Fitr starting Monday, but the parliament secretariat's
officials and employees get two days off only.
</P>
<P>
And after Eid, the parliament secretariat will function in
double shifts on week days for the smooth conduct of the winter
session and will work one shift even on Friday, one of the
country's two weekly holidays, the BSS said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
