<HEADLINE> Fog Affects Hainan Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- More than a hundred flights in
and out of Hainan's Haikou International Airport were canceled
today because of heavy fog blanketing this island province in
south China.
</P>
<P>
Visibility was down to 800 meters from early morning which is
unsuitable for normal taking off and landing procedures.
</P>
<P>
Some of the planes had to land in nearby airports in Guangdong
province and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, and the delayed
passengers have been sent on to Sanya Airport by bus.
</P>
<P>
The local weather bureau said that the fog might clear after
9:30 am tomorrow which will be a relief for airport authorities
who are expecting a further 155 flights on Tuesday. 
</P>
