<HEADLINE> Russia to Help Normalize U.S.-Cuba Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov said here Monday that Moscow is interested in developing
cooperation with Cuba and helping to enhance Cuba's ties with the
United States.
</P>
<P>
After talks with visiting Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto
Gonzalez, Ivanov stressed that Russia-Cuba relations were a
priority in his country's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
He said the two ministers had held a detailed discussion on
steps to further develop bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Russia would like to see Cuba and the U.S. entering
mutually-beneficial cooperation, Ivanov said.
</P>
<P>
"Moscow will be providing comprehensive assistance in the
establishment of such relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Robaina said he was satisfied with Monday's talks. "We
discussed a great deal of issues during a brief period," he said.
</P>
<P>
Robaina, who arrived here Sunday evening for a working visit,
is scheduled to meet with Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov
on Tuesday and pass on a message from Cuban President Fidel
Castro. 
</P>
</TEXT>
