<HEADLINE> 98-Year-Old Lonely Heart Receives 11 Responses of Marriage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Eleven women aged between 25
and 80 had by this afternoon responded to a marriage
advertisement made by a 98-year-old man a week ago.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kebiao, who was born in 1900, placed the advertisement
in the Shenjiang Service Herald, a newspaper in Shanghai. In the
advertisement he said that after the death of his wife in 1997 he
first felt free but gradually a year later found that he was
lonely and realized the profound truth that "half of a man is
woman"; thus he was seeking a companion to "banish his
loneliness."
</P>
<P>
Zhang included two stipulations: the woman must understand the
truth that "half of a woman is man" and she must be able to
communicate with him.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, a native of Haining City, Zhejiang Province, studied in
Japan and was awarded a doctoral degree when he was young. After
his return from Japan, he worked in Shanghai as editor of a
magazine, established a literature society, wrote essays and
fiction, and was well-known in the literary community of Shanghai
in the 1920s and 1930s.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Zhang lives in Haining and is able to take care of
himself. He asked a friend to place the marriage advertisement in
the Shanghai newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua has learned that the 11 respondents have all expressed
their respect for Zhang's knowledge and achievements and said
that they are willing to keep him company during the last years
of life.
</P>
<P>
"It won't matter if she is old or young and she can remarry
after my death,' Zhang said. He added that he is paid an average
of more than 700 yuan in retirement pension each month, which is
boosted by occasional author's fees.
</P>
<P>
A newspaper official said that the names of the respondents
will be forwarded to Zhang and appointments will be arranged in
accordance with his instructions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
