<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 13:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Calls for National Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei on Monday urged the Iranian nation to close ranks as
rival factions were bogged down in political quarrels over
mysterious murders of dissidents in the country.
</P>
<P>
Peace is a must in the country in order to solve the economic
problems of the people, Khamenei said at the ceremony to mark the
Eid Fitr, the last day of the Islamic fasting month of Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
He said that some people in the country are trying to harm the
unity of the nation by writing and saying futile things, the
Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian conservatives and moderates have been engaged in a
white-hot wrangling after the conservative-dominated Intelligence
Ministry admitted that some of its own agents were involved in
serial political murders of an opposition leader, his wife and
three dissident intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
The conservatives, who control most of the country's organs,
openly accused supporters of the moderate President Mohammad
Khatami of being behind the murders and attempting to seize the
Intelligence Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the moderates called for the resignation of
Intelligence Minister Qorbanali Dorri Najafabadi and a fundamental
change in the country's security and intelligence system
following the killings.
</P>
<P>
"The Muslim and revolutionary people of Iran respect all the
manifestations of unity and believe whatever that harms unity
comes from the devil," the Iranian leader said, "therefore, it is
essential that all gatherings throughout the country be held
peacefully and honorably."
</P>
<P>
Those who for their short-term interests, want to create a
wave in the pacific ocean of the Iranian nation and disturb the
people, should know that they will get nothing out of their
attempt, he said.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also expressed regret to the outbreak of tensions in
the course of Friday prayers congregations in certain cities over
the past year.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, a group of hard-liners attacked the Friday prayers
congregation in Isfahan and did not allow the pro-moderate Friday
prayers leader Ayatollah Jalaluddin Taheri to deliver his speech.
</P>
<P>
Taheri was forced to cancel the Friday prayers congregation
and his body guards were forced to shoot to the air after a group
of assailants cut off laud speakers and hurled objects to him.
</P>
<P>
Taheri, well-known for his support for President Khatami,
withdrew in October from the election of the Experts Assembly, a
powerful body to elect or dismiss the supreme leader, in a
protest to the conservative Guardian Council for disqualifying
moderate candidates.
</P>
<P>
However, Khamenei urged leaders of Friday prayers throughout
the country to refrain from raising issues which may result in
division and discord.
</P>
<P>
Following the admittance of the Intelligence Ministry, some
Friday prayers leaders called for an open trial on those arrested
in connection with political killings in order to find out those
behind the curtain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
