<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 24,087
international visitors seeking new products and the latest market
information flocked to the Hong Kong Toys and Games Fair '99 last
week, according to the fair's independent auditor, FKM of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC),
the fair was held from January 11 to 14 at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Total number of buyers increased by 71 percent, with buyers
from outside Hong Kong accounting for 48 percent of the total,
the auditor said.
</P>
<P>
