Taiwan, the Chinese mainland, South Korea, Australia, Germany,
the Philippines, Britain and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Young, chairman of the TDC's Toys Advisory Committee,
said the strong attendance reflects a growth in buyers'
confidence in the performance of the toy industry ahead.
</P>
<P>
Featuring 1,460 exhibitors from 25 countries and regions, the
Hong Kong Toys and Games Fair is the third largest toy fair
worldwide and the largest of its kind in Asia. The next fair will
be held in Hong Kong at the beginning of the year 2000.  
