<HEADLINE> China Provides Shortcut for Russian Tourists to Enter Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian tourists are now to be
allowed to cross China's mainland to enter and leave Hong Kong,
announced the Ministry of Public Security today which says the
measure is aimed at attracting more foreign tourists to the SAR.
</P>
<P>
According to the new ruling, made after an agreement between
relevant government departments in China's mainland and Hong
Kong, Russian tourists on a group transit visa leaving Hong Kong
for their homeland can for the first time travel through eleven
Chinese cities, which have been part of the opening up and reform
polices and include Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai, Guangzhou,
Haikou, Sanya, Shenzhen, Shenyang, Harbin, Qingdao and Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
The group visa has to be allocated by the department of border
entry and exist of the public security department by Chinese
travel services.
</P>
<P>
Only the China International Tourist Service and China Travel
Service are allowed to organize such tours, the agreement said;
their affiliated organizations are not allowed to conduct such
activities. 
</P>
