<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bahrain History to be on Show in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The three-month-long Bahrain
Delmon Exhibition to be staged in Paris on May 17 will provide
Europeans with a taste of Bahrain's rich history, the UAE's Gulf
News reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
All the archeological findings of the Delmon and Tylos eras
will be displayed to highlight Bahrain's image as the
archeological center of the Gulf, the daily quoted a senior
Bahraini official as saying in Bahraini capital Manama.
</P>
<P>
Arrangements are being made for the exhibition, which involve
cooperation between the Bahrain Ministry of Cabinet Affairs and
Information and the Arab World Institute in Paris, said
Abdullah Yateem, the Information Ministry's Undersecretary for
Culture and National Heritage.
</P>
<P>
From Paris the exhibition will move to the Danish city of
Aarhus, where the event will continue until the beginning of the
year 2000. The exhibition will also be held in London.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the Paris display in the Arab World Institute,
two smaller expositions will be held at the same place: a
five-week Bahrain Modern Art exhibition and a month-long
exhibition on the pearl industry.
</P>
<P>
The Paris exhibition will also include a symposium, where
researchers will speak on different aspects of Bahrain's
history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
