<HEADLINE> ITF Plans to Double Ban on Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ITF president Brian Tobin said on Monday that the increase
on penalty from currently one year to two years will come into
effect after next month's International Olympic
Committee (IOC) conference
</P>
<P>
Tobin said that ATP players met on Sunday to call for a
two-year ban after the women players gathered on Saturday to show
their backing of the proposed tougher bans, which is in
accordance with the Olympics standards set by the IOC.
</P>
<P>
The demand came after an ITF independent appeals committee did
not suspend Petr Korda who tested positive for the steroid
nandrolone at last year's Wimbledon Championships.
</P>
<P>
The ITF met with the IOC in December and was given until the
February 2-4 conference in Lausanne to reach a decision on a new
drugs code. 
