<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ambled
ahead Monday, gaining more than half of a U.S. cent amid renewed
optimism over the Brazilian economic situation.
</P>
<P>
World financial markets were buoyed by Brazil's decision on
Friday to float the real against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Scott Young, foreign exchange dealer of Arab Bank, said the
Australian currency, after trading little changed on Friday, along
with other world currencies, picked up on the floating news.
</P>
<P>
At the close of trading in Sydney Monday, the Australian dollar
was buying 63.69 U.S. cents from its close on Friday of 63.14 U.S.
cents.
</P>
<P>
During daytime trading it fell to a low of 63.43 U.S. cents and
reached a high of 63.71 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
At the close the Australian dollar was also buying 0.5498 euro
from 0.5390 euro Friday, and 72.58 Japanese yen from 71.14 yen,
while the euro was buying 1.1586 U.S. dollars from 1.1717 U.S.
dollars Friday. 
