<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Supervision of Insurance Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- China's insurance regulatory
authority announced today that it will adopt a series of new
measures to strengthen supervision of the insurance sector in
order to ensure good market order.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yongwei, chairman of the China Insurance Regulatory
Commission (CIRC), told Xinhua today that strict regulation will
be carried out in terms of both market practices and the
compensation capacity of insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that more effective regulation is a must due to t
he immaturity of China's insurance market, incomplete legal
system and insufficient self-control capacity of insurance
companies.
</P>
<P>
He said this year's regulatory efforts will focus on
rectifying the insurance market. Illegal insurance companies will
be banned and illegal activities will be dealt with severely
according to law.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC will strictly control the establishment of new
insurance companies over the next two years, according to Ma.
</P>
<P>
The intermediary insurance market will also be rectified, said
Ma, adding that illegal intermediary institutions will be banned
and individuals or organizations involved in illegal activities
will be subject to severe punishment.
</P>
<P>
He said the CIRC plans to ratify one or two professional
intermediary insurance institutions in order to standardize
related business activities gradually.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC will also strengthen regulation over the capital
conditions of insurance companies, reducing risks and perfecting
the legal system and various other key aspects of the sector,
said Ma.  
</P>
</TEXT>
