<HEADLINE> Architecture Industry to Use More Overseas Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Overseas edition of
People's Daily reported today that China's architecture industry
has pledged to use more overseas capital to renovate state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister of Construction Zheng Yijun said the industry
will introduce overseas capital to establish more knowledge- and
technology-intensive enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The government will continue to encourage a certain number of
large enterprises to adopt international administrative methods,
including public biding for projects instead of simply seeking
contracts for construction of projects. He added that the
industry will expand cooperation with overseas contracting
businesses.
</P>
<P>
Overseas capital had been used for more than 30,000
architecture projects by the end of 1997, with total contracts
valued at 15 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Construction companies from 14 countries and regions,
including the United Stated, Japan, the Republic of Korea,
Singapore and Germany, have established operations in China.
</P>
<P>
China has so far established 1,388 Sino-foreign joint ventures
in the architecture sector. 
</P>
