<DOCNO> XIE19990118.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin to Receive Medical Treatment, Doctors Say </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Doctors confirmed Monday that
Russian President Boris Yeltsin is suffering from a stomach ulcer
and should receive medical treatment, presidential spokesman
Dmitry Yakushkin said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that doctors at the Central Clinical
Hospital described Yeltsin's conditions as satisfactory. He
didn't specify what kind of medical treatment Yeltsin should
receive.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, 67, was hospitalized Sunday for acute gastric ulcer
bleeding. He will undergo treatment for two to three weeks, the
NTV television channel reported.
</P>
<P>
The president's poor health has again prompted calls for his
resignation and early elections. Yeltsin "is not in the condition
to perform his duties," Communist Party leader Gennady Zyuganov
said.
</P>
<P>
"For this reason, one should think how to turn them over to
the prime minister (Yevgeny Primakov) and the government and how
to elect a new president," Itar-Tass quoted Zyuganov as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, Yakushkin said there is no need for a transfer of
power and the "nuclear briefcase" as "the president can fully
perform his duties".
</P>
<P>
At the White House, site of the government, Primakov's
spokeswoman Tatyana Aristarkhova said there is no change in the
premier's schedule in connection with Yeltsin's hospitalization.
</P>
<P>
Primakov "has not received any additional instructions (from
Yeltsin)," Aristarkhova said.
</P>
<P>
Primakov will chair a routine meeting with his deputies and
meet with a delegation of the international conference of free
trade unions led by General Secretary Bill Jordan on Monday, she
said.
</P>
<P>
He will depart for Kazakhstan in the evening to attend the
inauguration ceremony of Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev on
January 20. Nazarbayev was reelected on January 10.
</P>
<P>
A visit to Davos to attend the international economic forum is
still on Primakov's agenda for January 29-31, Aristarkhova said.
</P>
</TEXT>
