<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visitors Arriving in Cambodia Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors
arriving at Phnom Penh International Pochentong Airport in 1998
decreased by more than 20 percent compared to 1997, latest
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the foreigners' affairs office of the Ministry of
Interior showed that the number of visitors coming to Cambodia in
1998 reached 212,951, a decrease of more than 40,000 compared with
255,124 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The visitors came from 126 countries and regions in the world.
Among them tourists reached about 151,476, businessmen at more
than 42,000 and official visitors less than 5,000, and about more
than 30 percent are from Asia.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of the leading sources of income for the
country. It is widely believed that more tourists and investors
will come here in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
