<HEADLINE> Seoul Stock Prices Up 7.95 Percent Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The share prices at the Seoul
stock market Monday rose 7.95 percent points, closing the day at
622.52 due to eased Brazil's financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the news that Standard and Poor's may have South
Korea's credit ratings upgraded next week also helped the stock
prices up.
</P>
<P>
A total of 289 shares valued 2.6 trillion won (some 2.2
billion U.S. dollars) changed hands Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers at 666 against 172 while 41 others
remained flat.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors bought shares worth 41.1 billion won while
retail player purchased 125.4 billion won. 
