<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Collectors Turn to Cartoon Books (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Works published before the Cultural Revolution mainly consist
of folklore and mysteries, with many of the books destroyed in
order to "eliminate feudalistic concepts". And the rarity of
related works has led to soaring prices.
</P>
<P>
Experts acknowledge that limited distribution of cartoon
books, compared to stamps, coins, and master paintings and
calligraphy pieces, offer collectors substantial investment
potential.
</P>
<P>
They also note that the value of cartoon books will possibly
surpass values for stamps and paintings over the next few years,
and their predict that the works will likely become a cultural
heritage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
