<HEADLINE> Shandong to Use More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
which ranks third in the nation in terms of gross domestic
product (GDP), plans to introduce more overseas funds for
infrastructure and basic industries this year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chuntao, director of the Provincial Commission of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, said the province will promote a
number of large overseas-funded projects during the year.
</P>
<P>
