<HEADLINE> Shanghai Consolidates Bus Manufacturing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's two largest bus
manufacturers, the Shanghai Bus Manufacturing Company and the
Shanghai Feiyi Automotive Co., Ltd., merged recently, with a
combined registered capital of 180 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the Municipal Economic Commission referred to the
move as a major step for this leading industrial city in its
attempt to build the auto industry into a pillar of the local
economy.
</P>
<P>
The new company, the Shanghai Bus Manufacturing Co., Ltd., is
co-funded by the Shanghai Automotive Industry Corporation, the
Shanghai Automotive Industry Co., Ltd. and the Shanghai Aircraft
Factory, with the Shanghai Automotive Industry Corporation
holding an 80.6 percent interest.
</P>
<P>
The new enterprise is aiming at an annual production capacity
of 3,000 buses and an equal number of chassis.
</P>
<P>
The merger is the second for the bus-manufacturing industry in
Shanghai. The first occurred two years ago, when several bus
factories were acquired by the Shanghai Bus Manufacturing
Company.  
</P>
