<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More State Firms in Tianjin Practice Democratic Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Eighty-five percent of Tianjin
Municipality's 3,000 state-owned enterprises have introduced a
system opening enterprise affairs to workers and practicing
democratic management since late 1997, and this system has proved
effective in combating various financial difficulties at these
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Now, more than 200 of the enterprises have been brought out of
the red or have reduced their losses, and 100 of them were
recently cited for outstanding performance in successfully
implementing the system.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the system includes holding
workers' congresses, joint conferences with the participation of
people representing the Party, the administrative departments and
trade unions, and publicizing the actual situations in the
enterprises to keep workers fully informed.
</P>
<P>
Through those methods, workers may discuss affairs including
major tasks and production decisions, the use of business
promotion fees, the distribution of bonuses and salaries, and the
appointment or removal of officials.
</P>
<P>
Based on opinions from workers' congresses, 467 officials of
these state-owned enterprises have been removed or suspended
temporarily from their original official posts, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that implementation of the system has also
made for a closer relationship between the enterprises and the
workers, and has aroused workers' initiative in caring for the
enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
