<HEADLINE> More People Shake off Poverty in Guizhou Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, January 18 Xinhua -- More than 1.81 million people in
southwest China's Guizhou Province escaped from poverty in 1998
with the help of governments of all levels, and the total number
of people in the province now living below the poverty line has
dropped to 2.75 million from 10 million in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Guizhou allocated 1.52 billion yuan (183
million U.S. dollars) for poverty-elimination programs in 1998.
The funds were mostly used to develop farming and breeding, and
water projects.
</P>
<P>
One effective method undertaken by the province was
encouraging local government officials to establish agreements
with poor families, offering them financial and technical
services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
