<HEADLINE> Yunnan Takes Measures to Reclaim Dianchi Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The 100 industrial enterprises
that release polluted water into Dianchi Lake in southwest
China's Yunnan Province will be closed unless they meet discharge
standards before May 1.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the provincial government's effort to improve
the lake's water quality before the start of the '99 Kunming
World Horticulture Exposition, which will be held in Kunming,
capital of the province, from May 1 to October 31.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to attract 88 countries and international
organizations and 10 million visitors from home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Located in southern Kunming, the freshwater lake covers an
area of 300 square kilometers and has become seriously polluted
due to rapid urbanization and industrialization over the past 20
years.
</P>
<P>
Dianchi lake has been listed as one of the country's key
rivers and lakes to be harnessed during the Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000) period.
</P>
<P>
Inspectors will be sent to 22 major polluting enterprises to
supervise the implementation of the plan created last Friday by
the province aimed at reclaiming the lake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
