<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Wanlin Arrested for Quackery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Infamous quack doctor Hu
Wanlin was recently arrested in the city of Shangqiu, central
China's Henan Province, for causing the deaths of more than 100
people.
</P>
<P>
Hu, 50, claimed to possess special skills enabling him to
clearly diagnose medical mysteries. The work "Qigong Master"
authored by Ke Yunlu provided Hu with instant fame and won a
large number of followers from at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Hu served two previous prison terms. He was released from
prison in 1997 and opened medical clinics in Taiyuan, capital of
north China's Shanxi Province, Zhongnanshan in Chang'an County,
in northwestern Shaanxi Province, and in Shanqiu, Henan Province.
Hu also engaged in an illegal medical practices in northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region and north China's Hebei
Province.
</P>
<P>
A number of Chinese researchers have published articles
strongly condemning Hu's quackery, with the assertions
revitalizing a nationwide campaign against pseudoscience.
</P>
<P>
Hu was arrested Shangqiu as a result of an arrest warrant
issued by the Suiyang District Procuratorate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
