<HEADLINE> China Sets Highway-Transportation Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese transport company
recently successfully sent four large pieces of equipment to
their destination, setting a record for the country's highway
transportation system in terms of size and weight.
</P>
<P>
The equipment was destined for the Qilu Petrochemical Company
based in the city of Zibo in east China's Shandong Province,
after being carried by ship to Shouguang, another Shandong city,
from Liaoning Province in the northeast.
</P>
<P>
The largest piece weighed 920 tons, and was 42.05 meters by
7.5 meters and 6.04 meters high.
</P>
<P>
The Jinan Motor Transport Company then dispatched a fleet of
motor vehicles to do the job, including one with a carrying
capacity of 1,300 tons that was specially imported from France.
</P>
<P>
About 23 bridges and 138 culverts along the 108-kilometer-long
road had been strengthened in advance for the journey.  
</P>
