<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
one of the country's economic powerhouses, has mapped out a plan
for its enterprises to promote operations abroad.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chuntao, director of the Provincial Commission of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, called this plan a part of the
province's effort to enhance its competitiveness in the
international market.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the province will encourage well-run
enterprise groups and listed companies to extend their business
operations to foreign countries.
</P>
