<HEADLINE> Three Killed, Two Injured in Fire in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed, two
others were injured and at least 2,000 shanties were gutted in a
devastating fire at a slum here on Sunday evening, press reports
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fire units from 10 stations rushed to the spot to extinguish
the blaze in Mohakhali, in the north part of the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the fire originated from domestic stove and
spread to the adjoining slum houses quickly. The fire devoured all
the shanties there, which were made of bamboo, straws, tin and
other materials, and provided shelter to some 10,000 dwellers.
</P>
<P>
In another fire incident, more than 100 shops were gutted at
Mirpur Cooperative Market in the city on Sunday afternoon, the
Bangladesh Observer daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which broke out in a hardware shop on the first floor
of the four-storied building, originated while some workers were
working with highly inflammable tincture in candle light at the
Luxmipur Hardware Shop, the report quoted fire fighters and police
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The fire spread to the adjoining shops quickly leaving more
than 60 shops gutted completely and 40 others partially. Only a
few shops on the same floor remained unaffected.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said a barrel full of tincture blasted with a bang
during the fire, fueling the flames and turning it as an inferno.
No deaths or injury was reported.
</P>
<P>
Shop owners said the fire spread to the adjacent shops so
quickly that they could not even remove the cash. "We have lost
everything," they said.
</P>
<P>
Some unscrupulous people, "in the name of helping fire
fighters," looted goods from the affected market during the
incident, according to the shop owners, who estimated the fire
damage at 80 million taka (1.65 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
