<HEADLINE> Naoto Kan Wins Japan's DPJ Leadership Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Naoto Kan, the incumbent leader
of the Democratic Party of Japan (DPJ), won the party leadership
race on Monday, beating Shigefumi Matsuzawa.
</P>
<P>
Kan won 180 votes while Matsuzawa took 51. There were two
invalid votes and six abstentions.
</P>
<P>
As many as 145 parliament members of the DPJ, the country's
largest opposition party, and 94 delegates from the party's
regional chapters were eligible to vote in the election.
</P>
<P>
Kan's victory was widely expected because of the backing he
received from the majority of the former members of the defunct
Amity Party and the former Socialist Party of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The DPJ merged last April with three minor opposition parties,
the Good Governance Party, the Amity Party and the Democratic
Reform Party. 
</P>
