<HEADLINE> Old Buddhist Frescos Found in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Several precious Buddhist
frescos dating back to the late Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) have
been found in an ancient temple in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Under a thick layer of white lime, the colorful frescos were
discovered on two walls of the Yuansheng Temple, which is
undergoing repair by the local historic relics department.
</P>
<P>
Archeologists say these frescos, featuring scenes from several
Buddhist stories including the birth of the Buddha, may be the
work of Qing Dynasty folk painters.
</P>
<P>
The well-preserved Yuansheng Temple was built in the Yuan
Dynasty (1271-1368). 
</P>
