<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 3.8 million Nepalese
children aged below five, who were administered polio drops on
December 7, 1998, were vaccinated again Monday under the
government's third immunization program.
</P>
<P>
Long queues were seen before some vaccination centers in
Kathmandu, the capital city.
</P>
<P>
A total of 23,000 centers were established around the country
for the service free of charge.
</P>
<P>
The government had declared Monday holiday for all government
offices and schools except the ministries and central-level
departments.
</P>
<P>
Some countries and international organizations are helping
Nepal in its efforts to eradicate polio, a disease which cripples
children, by the year 2000 as called upon by the World Health
Organization.
</P>
<P>
Nepali officials said that the immunization programs in the
past two years were successful. 
