envisages new government borrowing of 33.3 billion dollars,
according to a government sources on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Expenditures are due to increase to 288.76 billion dollars
from 270.36 billion dollars the year before as Finance Minister
Oskar Lafontaine refrains from making deep cuts in the social
services sector, reports of the German Press Agency said.
