</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- An anti-money laundering law, the first of its
kind in Romania, took effect on Sunday for the crackdown of
rampant under-world economy, which amounts to 22 percent of the
country's gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Exchange and transfer of money made through illegal deals
such as drug trafficking, smuggling, theft, fraud and tax evasion
are listed as money laundering in the law. (Romania-Anti-Money
Laundering) 
