<HEADLINE> Thai Airways Flies Shrimps to Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Thai shrimp exporters have
chartered a Thai Airways International (THAI) plane to fly shrimps
to Shanghai, aviation sources said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
That will be the first shipment of shrimps bound for the
metropolitan city.
</P>
<P>
Normally, THAI reserves about half of the 40 tons of cargo
space on selected passenger flights for loading farm products.
Being able to double the amount of farm cargo will be a boom to
exporters, said the sources on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
Most of the shrimps exported to Shanghai are fresh, and bring
in more revenue than frozen products, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The exporters has signed a one-year contract with THAI for the
use of the plane, which will not carry passengers.
</P>
<P>
After the Shanghai run, the plane will be used to export other
products such as durian, rambutan, longan and fresh flowers to
other markets, especially Hong Kong and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The exporters also want to maximize the utilization of the
plane by finding goods to ship back to Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
