<HEADLINE> Thailand's Telecom Liberalization Plan Set to be Delayed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Transport Ministry opposed the council's contention that
changes could delay setting up the NCC scheduled for late this
year, thus affecting liberalization.
</P>
<P>
In addition there is a conflict between the Transport Ministry
and Finance Ministry on the privatization of two state telecom
carriers, the Telephone Organization of Thailand (TOT) and the
Communications Authority of Thailand (CAT), and on the conversion
of telecom concession contracts.
</P>
<P>
The Transport Ministry wants to integrate the TOT and CAT in
the form of a holding company, but the Finance Ministry argues
that the TOT and CAT should establish holding companies separately
to prevent a monopoly during liberalization.
</P>
<P>
Concession conversion has been put on hold by the state
Enterprise Policy Committee, chaired by Deputy prime Minister and
Commerce Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi.
</P>
<P>
The committee selected the Thailand Development Research
Institute to conduct the conversion study within the next two
months in preparation for a public hearing. 
