<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Political Parties Demand OSCE Mission Head's Removal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav political parties
Sunday strongly condemned William Walker, chairman of the Kosovo
Verification Mission of the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe, for lying about the latest development in
Kosovo and demanded his immediate removal.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian Socialist Party, in a statement, expressed its
"strongest" condemnation of Walker's remarks, saying that the
whole world in the past few months has seen clearly that ethnic
Albanian "terrorists" are the only obstacle to a peaceful
solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
While ethnic Albanian "terrorists" have repeatedly slaughtered
and kidnapped civilians, Serb policemen, Yugoslav service men and
even members of the OSCE Kosovo Verification Mission, Walker has
all along kept silence, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The only explanation to Walker's silence is that he is the
ally of the ethnic Albanian "terrorists," it said.
</P>
<P>
The party urged the Kosovo Verification Mission to report
subjectively to the international community on what is happening
in Kosovo. It also asked the international community to ease
supporting the Albanian "terrorists" in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav Lefties Coalition said through its spokesman that
Walker told lies for the purpose of provoking new international
pressure on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Considering the fact that Walker has become the spokesman and
protector of the ethnic Albanian "terrorists," it said, he no
longer has the right to serve as head of the OSCE Kosovo Mission.
</P>
<P>
Golan Latinovik, chairman of the Supreme Committee of the
Yugoslav Communist Party, said at a press conference that the
United Stated intends to use the OSCE as a tool for it to
dominate the world and Walker is the executor of this intention.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian Radical Party also issued a statement demanding
the OSCE leadership to dismiss Walker right away.
</P>
<P>
It said that Walker's hatred of the Serb Republic and people
is by no means less than that of the "terrorist groups" in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
His continued serving as mission chairman will only further
worsen the situation in Kosovo and throw into question the
existence of the OSCE Kosovo Verification Mission, it said.
</P>
<P>
According to reports of the Yugoslav news agency Tanjug, the
Serb police were forced to exchange fire with illegal Albanian
militants last Friday in the village of Racak, South Kosovo,
killing at least 15 militants.
</P>
<P>
Walker announced Saturday in Pristina that after his
on-the-spot verification, he was sure that the Yugoslav police
force had killed 45 ethnic Albanian civilians in Racak. Walker
also asked the U.N. war crime tribunal in the Hague to send
investigators to Racak within 24 hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
