<HEADLINE> Northwest Xinjiang Cracks Down on Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Urumqi Customs Office in
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous region handled more
than 700 smuggling cases and confiscated goods worth 30 million
yuan (3.6 million U.S. dollars) in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Over the past six months, customs focused its efforts on
smuggling cases involving drugs, vehicles, falcons, weapons and
ammunitions, and other illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
Last April, Horgos Customs on the Chinese-Khazakstan border
seized six pistols, a submachine gun and 2,000 rounds of
ammunition hidden in a truck. This was the largest smuggling case
involving military weapons ever discovered in China.
</P>
<P>
Urumqi customs officials also discovered 11 false customs
declarations worth 310 million yuan (38.6 million dollars) last
year. 
</P>
