<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Foreign Trade Maintains Steady Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province, one of the country's giants, scored a foreign trade
volume of 130 billion U.S. dollars in 1998, equaling its figure
for the previous year, according to Guangdong Provincial Customs.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's trade volume accounted for 40 percent of the
country's total, according to statistics.
</P>
<P>
The province's export volume for 1998 stood at 75.72 billion
U.S. dollars, a slight increase of 1.5 percent over 1997; and
exports to all continents scored increases except for exports to
other Asian countries, which dropped by 5.6 percent. Export
commodities from Guangdong included clothing, shoes, furniture,
toys and plastic products.
</P>
<P>
Total import volume for 1998 reached 54.28 billion U.S.
dollars, a drop of 2.2 percent from 1997, with import commodities
including plastic raw materials, rolled steel, micro-electronic
components, paper plates, equipment parts, copper materials and
crude oil. 
</P>
