<HEADLINE> Shanghai Cracks Down on Liquor Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Customs recently
cracked a smuggling case involving five-million-yuan worth of
liquors shipped from abroad, the first of its kind in 50 years.
</P>
<P>
It was also the first case of smuggling brought to light in
the city this year. Among the seized liquors were foreign-made
wine, brandy and several brands of whisky.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that the liquors were smuggled by a suspect
with a family name of Zhang working for a Shanghai representative
office of a Hong Kong company. The case is still under
investigation and Zhang has been summoned to court.
</P>
<P>
As one of the country's vital ports, Shanghai stands pledged
to end all smuggling activities. 
