<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Projects Growth Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU,January 18(Xinhua) -- Determined to maintain
its growth momentum, Guangzhou,capital of the prosperous south
coastal province of Guangdong,is eyeing a 13 percent GDP growth
for 1999, the same rate as the previous year.
</P>
<P>
With a 15 percent yearly increase in investment, the city
expects to achieve a growth of 4.5 percent in the agricultural
sector, 12.5 percent in industrial sectors and 14.5 percent in
service businesses.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 20 years, the city's economy has expanded by an
average annual rate of 14.26 percent, 4.64 percentage points
higher than the national average. Last year, the city's GDP rose
by 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
Pressed by the fallout of the Asia financial crisis, the city
will focus on developing its domestic market. The investment
priorities will include infrastructure, hi-tech industries,
economical housing and technical innovation, according to Lin
Shusen, Guangzhou's mayor.
</P>
<P>
The city will also make efforts to increase its export and
step up supervision over the financial and banking sectors to
prevent financial risks, the mayor noted. 
</P>
