<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Consumers Expected to Spend More on Expensive Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Cars, home decoration, travel
and cosmetics are among the ten hot consumer items on which most
Chinese are likely to spend their money in the next two years.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey done by concerned departments and rep
orted by China Travel News, durable goods lead the list and
demand for cameras, video-game players, bicycles, and electric
cookers is expected to grow by ten percent, while that of
wide-screen televisions, fully-automatic washing machines,
air-conditioners, and video-cameras will rise substantially.
</P>
<P>
Telephone sales are also expected to boost telecommunications
industry, which will also see a burgeoning market for fax
machines and mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
More urbanites expect to travel and take part in sports, which
will lead to a boom of sports clubs.
</P>
<P>
New life-styles and increased income will trigger a higher
demand for fast food and for cosmetics, beauty and health
products.
</P>
<P>
The swelling in the aged group will push up the consumption of
health food, tonics and medicine for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
Other growth points include insurance and housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
