<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Compatriots Find Marrow for Mainland College Student </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-two marrow matches
for the same type as that of a university student in southwest
China's Chongqing Municipality have been found in Taiwan in the
past week, according to Taiwan sources.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua released a story on December 17 last year about how
people are giving a helping hand to Zhang Yu, a female student at
Chongqing Normal University, who was diagnosed with acute
aplastic anemia last October.
</P>
<P>
At present, China has marrow bases in Beijing, Shanghai and Gu
angzhou, but no same-type marrow as that of Zhang was found at
any of these facilities.
</P>
<P>
The Tzu Chi Taiwan Marrow Donor Registry has selected 22
marrow records from 160,000 on file since Zhang's records were
transferred to the center at the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Xinqiao Hospital, where Zhang Yu is now a patient, has
selected 14 donors from the 22 based on age, sex and health
conditions.
</P>
<P>
More work is needed to find five other people who have the
same type HLA as Zhang, according to hospital sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
