<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningbo To Build Large Tunnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- An agreement to build a tunnel
in Ningbo in east China's Zhejiang Province has been signed.
Construction will cost nearly 400 million yuan and the tunnel
will be the largest urban infrastructure project ever undertaken
in the city.
</P>
<P>
The project includes a 1,300-meter-long tunnel, called the
Changhong, with nearly 2,000 meters of highway at either end.
</P>
<P>
Work on the project will begin in the first half of this year
and is scheduled to be completed at the end of 2001.
</P>
<P>
Construction includes the building of eight traffic lanes and
is expected to ease traffic jams in the local downtown area and
ameliorate the traffic between downtown and the local rural
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
