<HEADLINE> China Renovates largest Detergent Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- China has finished renovating
its largest detergent project at a company in the old industrial
province of Liaoning, which is expected to double the production
capacity of the nation's top producer of chemicals used to sy
nthesize detergents.
</P>
<P>
The company, located in the major industrial city of Fushun,
is the largest of its kind in Asia and the third largest in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Launched in 1995, the renovation project cost 150 million
yuan, and is expected to increase the company's annual output to
144,000 tons.  
</P>
