<HEADLINE> Huber Beats Spirlea in Australian Open First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Anke Huber of Germany
eliminated 13th seed Irina Spirlea of Romania in the first round
of the Australian Open tennis at Melbourne on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Huber, quarterfinalist here in 1991 and 1992,
finalist in 1996 and semifinalist last year, stormed to a 7-5,
6-4 victory and now will play 21-year-old Sylvia Plischke of
Austria who beat Kvela Hrdlickova of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Spirlea, whose game revolves around a big serve and blistering
forehand, could rely on neither of her main weapons on Monday.
She also made 47 unforced errors to Huber's 23.
</P>
<P>
Spirlea was beaten in the first round last year by Serena
Williams of the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
