<HEADLINE> Schlesser and Sainct Win Titles at Dakar Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Frenchmen Jean-Louis Schlesser,
driving a Schlesser buggy, won the car section and his compatriot
Richard Sainct on a BMW, captured the motorcycle title at the
Dakar Rally after the 16th and final stage on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The car section of the 260km last stage between Saint-Louis
and Dakar, with just a 20km special stage, was won by the Nissan
of Spain's Salvador Servia, though the motorcycle section was
canceled.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time Schlesser and Sainct, both finishing hig
h up in previous legs, won the prestigious rally which started
from Grenada in Spain on January 1.
</P>
<P>
The 16 stages totalled 9,000km with 5,770km of special stages
mainly in the desert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
