<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,500 Year-old Coins Unearthed in Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Archeologists from Chinese
prestigious Beijing University recently found eight ancient coins
dating from the Song Kingdom during the Northern and Southern
Dynasties period (420-589) in Zhongxian County in southwest Chin
a's Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The eight well-preserved coins were discovered in a brick tomb
near the Yajiao ruins in the Three Gorges Reservoir area in the
middle reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
 Along with the coins, they also found porcelain and silver
utensils and two pearls, the smallest with a diameter of only one
millimeter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
