<HEADLINE> Germany Wins Four-man Bobsled Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Christoph Langen of Germany
clocked the fastest times in both runs to win the title of a
four-man World Cup bobsled race at Winterberg, Germany, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was Langen's seventh victory this season. He put up a
disappointing performance in Saturday's two-man competition.
</P>
<P>
The Germans clocked 54.25 seconds in the first run and 54.58
in the second for a winning total of 1:48.83.
</P>
<P>
Marcel Rohner of Switzerland finished second at 1:49.48,
followed by another German Harald Czudaj in the third place at
1:49.59. 
</P>
