<HEADLINE> Finland's Ahonen Scores Fifth Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Janne Ahonen claimed
his fifth victory of the season on Sunday, extending his
domination in 12 of 16 World Cup events in Zakopane, Poland.
</P>
<P>
Ahonen leapt 119.0 meters and then achieved the day's longest
jump with 128.5 meters, on the 116-meter Zakopane hill. Olympic
champion Kazuyoshi Funaki of Japan jumped 119.0 and 121.5 meters
to place second.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Ahonen has 1,223 World Cup points this season,
345 more than his closest rival, Martin Schmitt of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Austria's Stefan Horngacher, winner of the Zakopane
competition on Saturday, placed third with leaps of 121.0 and
116.5 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
