<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukrainan, Kenyan Win Houston Marathon Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Tatiana Pozdnyakova of
Ukraine and Stephen Ndungu of Kenya won the women's and men's
titles respectively at the Houston marathon race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pozdnyakova, who won the 1996 Houston marathon but was
disqualified for using a banned substance, overcame slippery
streets and humidity to win the women's title.
</P>
<P>
Pozdnyakova clocked 2 hours 33 minutes and 23 seconds to take
the title. It was Pozdnyakova's third win at Houston. She also
claimed the title in 1995 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
Zinaida Semenova of Russia finished second at 2:36:23,
followed by Elfenseh Alemu of Ethiopia in the third place at
2:37:05.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Ndungu successfully defended the men's title with a
time of 2 hours, 14 minutes and 56 seconds, leading a 1-2-3 Ken
yan finish.
</P>
<P>
Ndungu beat his compatroit Sammy Maritim and Gideon Mutisya to
the second and third places respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
