<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Wishes Yeltsin Quickly Recovers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The White House wished
Russian President Boris Yeltsin will recover from ulcer quickly on
Sunday after he was taken to a hospital with a bleeding ulcer.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that he recovers quickly," White House spokesman P.J.
Crowley said.
</P>
<P>
"Meanwhile, as the Kremlin indicated last year, Prime Minister
(Yevgeny) Primakov continues to handle the day-to-day affairs of
the government,"said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
A Kremlin spokesman said Yeltsin was at Moscow's Central
Clinical Hospital, where he was in stable condition after tests
confirmed that he had a bleeding ulcer, the latest in a series of
severe ailments that have plagued him.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin would be kept in hospital for the next few days, the
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
